OL,6,FThe jury was also shown pages of a
OL,7,Fnotebook that was found at the
OL,8,Fdefendant's home. Inside were drawings
OL,9,Fof Ms Elias and the pupil who was
OL,10,Fstabbed.
OL,12,FPassages were also read out in which
OL,13,Fthe defendant had written, 'I want to
OL,14,Fdo something humans are not supposed
OL,15,Fto?' and 'Why do I want to kill others
OL,16,Fas much as I want to kill myself?'
OL,18,FIn one of the final excerpts written
OL,19,Funder the heading 'Things about me,'
OL,20,Fthe girl had written 'I feel like I'm
OL,21,Fgoing to commit a crime of a lifetime.'
